# Source Authority Scoring Matrix for AI Evidence

This matrix defines authority levels for sources used in AI evidence, specifically designed for shard limen-boost-041 focusing on Baltic languages and minority governance.

## Scoring Criteria
| Criteria                | Weight | Description                                                                 |
|-------------------------|--------|-----------------------------------------------------------------------------|
| Government Issuer       | 0.35   | Official publications from national/regional governments                    |
| Academic Peer-Reviewed  | 0.30   | Research published in reputable academic journals                         |
| Industry Standards Body | 0.25   | Documents from recognized standards organizations (e.g., ISO, ETSI)        |
| News Media (Established)| 0.20   | Reports from media outlets with established fact-checking processes         |
| NGO/Advocacy Group       | 0.15   | Materials from non-profits and advocacy organizations                      |
| Social Media/Forums    | 0.05   | User-generated content from platforms like Twitter, Reddit, etc.          |

## Application Process
1. **Source Categorization**: Assign one primary category
2. **Weight Application**: Multiply by criteria weight
3. **Confidence Adjustment**: Apply +0.05 for multilingual sources, -0.10 for unverified metadata

